==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interposition
<hw>In`ter*po*si"tion</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>interpositio</ets> a putting between, insertion, fr.
<ets>interponere</ets>, <ets>interpositum</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>interposition</ets>. See <er>Interpone</er>,
<er>Position</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of interposing, or the state of being
interposed; a being, placing, or coming between; mediation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The thing interposed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interposure</ent>⟦br⟧
